# Global Engineering Defaults

- Make the smallest safe change that satisfies the request.
- Follow repository-local conventions before introducing new patterns.
- Prefer explicit failure paths over silent fallback behavior.
- Keep changes testable and update tests for behavior changes.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly requested.
- When commit work is requested, prefer atomic commits split by concern for easy review and cherry-picking.
